To help you understand their health management

Always take part in various kinds of suitable intense exercises. You should ensure that your body is comfortable and not fatigued. The recommended workout duration is 30-60 minutes of exercise at least 3 times per week. To prevent injury, do not exercise for more than 1 hour at a time.
Listening to music can help with mental exhaustion by creating a lighter mood and encourage relaxation after physical exertion.

Reading regularly may help you live longer as well as confer other benefits to your mental state. Reading books can improve your memory, focus and concentration, reduce stress, and help you sleep better.
After hard work you should pay attention to rest and relaxation; health is the most important thing.
Let Wearfit app record your health status so that you can develop a healthy lifestyle.
Condition is good, please continue to keep fit, drink plenty of water, have regular exercise and relaxation so that your health status is maintained.
Feeling tired? Stop to rest, take a deep breath, repose, adopt a relaxed mood, adjust state of mind, forget your troubles, adopt a simple way of life or let oneself have a relaxing space.

Getting sufficient sleep regularly is important to your health. It helps your mind and body stay healthy. A minimum of 6 hours uninterrupted sleep each night will help reduce your risk of heart attack while 8-10 hours sleep can help improve your stamina and concentration, prevent stress and reduce depression. Exercise, walking, healthy eating, relaxation and social interaction will help improve your ability to sleep well.
"Staying up late, smoking and drinking will speed up the resting heart rate. Don't drink caffeine, which can cause insomnia easily. Regular excretion helps to maintain a smooth metabolic system."
Obesity will increase the burden on the heart and speed up the heart rate. Obese people should exercise more and adjust their diet to attain a healthier weight.
Keep the mind calm, do not always worry or become angry. If, because of tension or anxiety, the heart rate is too fast, listen to music or practice meditation as ways to gradually restore calm.

Regular walking exercises can reduce excess fat and improve fitness and strength. Walking may also help with headaches, backache, shoulder pain, etc. and promote sleep. Experts suggest that adults should take walking exercises daily as a way of keeping fit to maintain health.

By wearing an smart bracelet with realtime readings of blood pressure and heart rate data, you can observe your heart condition anywhere at anytime. When feeling any persistent discomfort, it is better to stop self-monitoring and see a health professional.

When outdoors regularly, walking in nature, the fresh air and surrounding beauty can help a person feel relaxed, restrain low moods, improve the excitability of the central nervous system, or help a person be in a good mental state with improved energy levels.
"Emotions are normal, but try to remain calm. Focus on the moment, keep in touch with family and friends, don't miss opportunities to tell people that you love them."

Positive social interaction can enhance a physical and mental health. Lack of social interation can lead to becoming over-weight and developing high blood pressure. Good social interation is as beneficial as regular exercise. Together they can lead to a longer and healthier life.

When heart rate is under 60bpm (over 45bpm), it is called sinus bradycardia which occurs in people engaged in heavy manual labour for a long period or athletes. It can also be found in low thyroid function, intracranial hypertension, cholangetic jaundice and application of Quinidine and Propranolol drugs. Please check the cause of the disease with a health professional.

Heart rate is slightly fast. When heart rate is over 100bpm (under 160bpm) it is called nodal tachycardia which can be caused by excitement, stress, smoking and drinking alcohol or caffeine. It can also be found in fever, shock, anemia, hyperthyroidism, heart failure and applications of atropine or epinephrine (adrenaline). Please check the cause of the disease with a health professional.

When heart rate is under 40bpm, also consider sick sinus syndrome or atrioventricular block. Where an abnormal heart rhythm characterized by rapid and irregular beating is present, atrial fibrillation should be considered.
"The heart rate of healthy adults may differ significantly. Heart rate will be affected by age, gender and other physiological conditions. Normal range： 60-100bpm Resting range: 60-80bpm"
When heart rate is around 160-220bpm it is called paroxysmal tachycardia. Please visit a hospital for a detailed examination.
Please rest, let the body and mind to relax, long-term overwork can make the body burden.
